# Convex Function Patterns for Agent Court

## Function Types

- **Mutations**: Write to database (cases, evidence, rulings, votes)
- **Queries**: Read from database (case details, stats, judge info) 
- **Actions**: External calls, complex logic, engine processing
- **HTTP Actions**: API endpoints for external agents

## Error Handling Pattern

Always use try-catch with detailed logging:

```typescript
try {
  console.info(`Processing ${operation} for ${identifier}`);
  // ... operation logic
  console.info(`${operation} result: ${result}`);
  return result;
} catch (error) {
  console.error(`${operation} failed for ${identifier}:`, error);
  throw new Error(`${operation} failed: ${error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error)}`);
}
```

## Database Query Pattern

Use type annotations for query callbacks:
```typescript
.withIndex("by_field", (q: any) => q.eq("field", value))
```

## Judge Agent Integration

Judge agents are **functions**, not separate services:
- Analysis logic in mutations/actions
- Simple hardcoded logic for MVP (replace with LLM calls later)
- Panel voting via standard mutations

## No External Dependencies

- Constitution rules: hardcoded in [constitution.ts](mdc:apps/convex/constitution.ts)
- MCP tools: HTTP endpoints in [http.ts](mdc:apps/convex/http.ts)  
- Evidence processing: built into mutations
- Transparency: Convex actions calling Rekor